social_posts.post_text: now & then…took these photos exactly one year apart! can’t believe it’s been 6 whole months with our precious girl. we love you, Margot! 🫶🏼

Mother’s Day // the past 7 months have been some of the most wonderful, exhausting, happiest, and amazing times of my life. I wrote down some things I wish I could have told my pregnant self: 
- you’ll stop throwing up eventually, I promise. 
- your birth doesn’t go as planned, but it’s beautiful in its own way because you and Margot are okay. 
- John is the best dad. Even better than you could have imagined.
- Buy jeans in your new size 
- You’re gonna tell your birth story to a room full of strangers; and those strangers are going to become your friends. 
- don’t worry about the nursery being perfect 
- Buy the blackout curtains, they’re ugly but she’ll sleep better 
- There is no better sound than the sound of Margot’s giggle
- Your life is about to turn upside down, but it will be pretty awesome.
 Happy Mother’s Day to all the moms out there, there is no greater gift 💕 thanks for making me a mama, margot.
Father’s Day weekend but it was really about our outfits 🌺
by the way, we’re going out tonight ✨ such a fun weekend celebrating love, congrats @waytobea & @james_few 🌼💗
mom & dad’s first weekend away 🌸 congrats to the Hermans, we love you!
come back stronger than a 90s trend 🖤

summer memories 💫 // traveling with Margot and seeing her grow up and become her own little person this summer was  the most rewarding experience and I can’t believe I have the privilege of being her mom 💛 it has truly been the light at the end of the tunnel while working on healing myself from a traumatic birth and PPD- this has kept me offline because being vulnerable on the internet (or really anywhere other than therapy) makes me cringe. but, it is wild to experience the highs of being a mom and the lows of losing your confidence, ptsd and feeling isolated. I’m choosing to celebrate the little wins lately, like having time to make this post. (btw- don’t worry this is still largely a fashion page, can’t wait to share more fits and fun finds soon. ok, bye!)

NY recap: 🛍️🍸👯‍♀️🤳🏼🎀 // lost bags, missed shows, meeting internet friends IRL, shopping (lots and lots of shopping), finally seeing the @treasuresofnyc showroom, having bestie time with the one and only @phongsaintjames, getting 9 hours of uninterrupted sleep in the middle of a king size bed, finally being reunited with my suitcase only 5 hours before flying home- this trip was anything but boring ❤️‍🔥 will surely tell Margot about it one day when she asks why mommy only flies with carry ons.

back on the grid, hi! 🫶🏼
